-- S. Africa Reinforce Steel Dearth to Curb Building, Bus. Day Says
-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 2011-02-10T05:26:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-10/south-africa-reinforce-steel-dearth-to-curb-building-business-day-reports.html
South Africa’s construction industry
faces a shortage of reinforcing steel that may stall projects 
after the breakdown last month of ArcelorMittal  South Africa  
Ltd.’s furnace in Newcastle, KwaZulu-Natal curbed supply, 
Business Day reported.   Reinforcing steel won’t be available this month, possibly
halting projects and causing delays, the Johannesburg-based
newspaper said, citing Rod Mountford, director of the South
African Reinforced Concrete Engineers Association.     To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  